# Freyra T4 Memory Rules

## VRAM Budget (15GB total)

| Component | VRAM |
|-----------|------|
| SDXL UNet fp8 | ~3.3 GB |
| CLIP encoders fp16 | ~1.5 GB |
| VAE fp16 | ~0.3 GB |
| GPT-2 expansion | ~0.3 GB |
| 2 LoRAs | ~0.5 GB |
| Face adapter (IP-Adapter) | ~1-2 GB |
| **Inference workspace** | **~6-8 GB** |

## Hard Constraints

- `minimum_inference_memory()` = 4 GB floor
- Max 2 LoRAs simultaneously loaded
- fp8 UNet (`--unet-in-fp8-e4m3fn`), fp16 VAE
- Resolution cap: 896x1152 portrait, 1024x1024 square
- Refiner always disabled (saves ~3GB)

## Memory Cleanup Protocol

- Call `aggressive_empty_cache()` (gc.collect + cuda.empty_cache + synchronize) between pipeline stages
- Delete intermediate tensors (`del task['c'], task['uc']`) after sampling
- Face analyzer runs on CPU, embeddings cached, adapter loaded only during conditioning
- Unload face adapter before VAE decode
